  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Wash the rice two or three times until the water runs clear, then drain. Add the rice to a lidded saucepan along with the coconut milk and a pinch of salt, and give it a good stir. Bring the mixture to a boil over a high heat (you might need to give it another stir as the coconut solids melt) then cover with a lid, reduce to the lowest heat and set the timer for 18 mins. When the time is up, turn off the heat and leave the lid on until ready to serve."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Finely mince the garlic and chilli (this dish is spicy so use half the specified amount for less heat). Heat a glug of vegetable oil in a large frying pan or wok set over a high heat. Add the garlic and chilli and stir fry for 20 seconds until fragrant. Add the prawns and fry for a further 1-2 mins. Add the nam prik pao paste, white sugar, fish sauce, oyster sauce and water. Stir fry for a minute until the sauce ingredients have combined and coated the prawns. Add the Thai basil leaves and a handful of spinach. Stir fry for a couple of minutes until wilted. If the sauce is too dry, add a splash more water."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "To serve, divide the rice between plates and top with the prawns and sauce. Finish with a wedge of lime."
    }
  ],
